# 📌 Task 1 — Design a College Management System

## 1️⃣ Student Object

**Purpose:** Stores student information.

| Field Name | Description |
|---|---|
| Student Name | Name of the student |
| Roll Number | Unique roll number |
| Email | Student email address |
| Phone Number | Contact number |
| Date of Birth | Birth date of student |
| Address | Residential address |
| Percentage | Academic percentage |
| Department | Related department |

---

## 2️⃣ Faculty Object

**Purpose:** Stores faculty information.

| Field Name | Description |
|---|---|
| Faculty Name | Name of faculty member |
| Employee ID | Unique employee ID |
| Email | Faculty email |
| Subject Specialization | Expert subject area |
| Salary | Faculty salary |
| Department | Associated department |

---

## 3️⃣ Course Object

**Purpose:** Stores course information.

| Field Name | Description |
|---|---|
| Course Name | Name of course |
| Course Code | Unique course code |
| Credits | Course credits |
| Total Seats | Total available seats |
| Filled Seats | Seats already filled |
| Faculty Assigned | Assigned faculty member |

---

## 4️⃣ Department Object

**Purpose:** Stores department details.

| Field Name | Description |
|---|---|
| Department Name | Name of department |
| HOD Name | Head of department |
| Department Block | Department building/block |
| Total Students | Total students count |

---

## 5️⃣ Enrollment Object (Junction Object)

**Purpose:** Connects Students and Courses.

| Field Name | Description |
|---|---|
| Student | Related student |
| Course | Related course |
| Enrollment Date | Date of enrollment |
| Marks | Student marks |
| Attendance | Attendance percentage |

---

# 🔗 Relationships

## 1️⃣ Department → Student

- **Relationship Type:** Lookup Relationship
- One Department can have many Students.

### Example

```text
CSE Department
   ├── Student 1
   ├── Student 2
   └── Student 3
```

---

## 2️⃣ Department → Faculty

- **Relationship Type:** Lookup Relationship
- One Department can have many Faculty members.

---

## 3️⃣ Faculty → Course

- **Relationship Type:** Lookup Relationship
- One Faculty can teach many Courses.

---

## 4️⃣ Student ↔ Course

- **Relationship Type:** Many-to-Many Relationship
- Implemented using Enrollment Object.

### Explanation

- One student can enroll in many courses.
- One course can contain many students.

---

# 📌 Final Relationship Structure

```text
Department
   ↓
Students

Department
   ↓
Faculty

Faculty
   ↓
Courses

Student ↔ Enrollment ↔ Course
```

