# 💭 Task 4 — Reflection Task

## Why do companies need structured data instead of random spreadsheets?

Companies prefer structured data systems because they are more organized, secure, scalable, and efficient than random spreadsheets.

---

## 1️⃣ Better Organization

Structured systems store data in objects, fields, and relationships. This makes information easier to find and manage.

---

## 2️⃣ Reduced Errors

Spreadsheets often contain duplicate data, missing values, and formula mistakes. Structured systems use validation rules and automation to reduce errors.

---

## 3️⃣ Faster Reporting

Companies can quickly generate reports such as:

- Student performance
- Course enrollment
- Faculty workload
- Department statistics

---

## 4️⃣ Improved Security

Structured systems provide role-based access control so only authorized users can access specific information.

---

## 5️⃣ Automation

Systems like Salesforce support:

- Automatic calculations
- Notifications
- Workflows
- Dashboards

This reduces manual work and saves time.

---

## 6️⃣ Scalability

Spreadsheets may work for small datasets, but large organizations need systems that can handle thousands of records efficiently.

